@### GitHub Commands:-

# 1. Typical Git Workflow Example(From global to local):

git clone <repo>
git status
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git push origin main

# 2. Typical Git Workflow Example(From local to global):

git init
git status
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin <repo>
git push -u origin main

______________________________________________
# Setup & Configuration:

| Command                                  | Use                     |
| ---------------------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| `git config --global user.name "Name"`   | Set your username       |
| `git config --global user.email "email"` | Set your email          |
| `git config --list`                      | View current Git config |
| `git help <command>`                     | Get help for a command  |

______________________________________________
# Creating & Getting Repositories:

| Command           | Use                         |
| ----------------- | --------------------------- |
| `git init`        | Create a new Git repository |
| `git clone <url>` | Copy an existing repository |

______________________________________________
# Basic Workflow (Most Important):

| Command                    | Use                          |
| -------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `git status`               | Check file changes and state |
| `git add <file>`           | Stage a file                 |
| `git add .`                | Stage all changes            |
| `git commit -m "message"`  | Save staged changes          |
| `git commit -am "message"` | Add & commit tracked files   |
| `git log`                  | View commit history          |
| `git log --oneline`        | Short commit history         |

______________________________________________
# Branching:

| Command                    | Use                  |
| -------------------------- | -------------------- |
| `git branch`               | List branches        |
| `git branch <name>`        | Create a branch      |
| `git checkout <branch>`    | Switch branches      |
| `git checkout -b <branch>` | Create & switch      |
| `git switch <branch>`      | Modern way to switch |
| `git merge <branch>`       | Merge a branch       |
| `git branch -d <branch>`   | Delete a branch      |

______________________________________________
# Remote Repositories (GitHub, GitLab, etc.)

| Command                       | Use                   |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------- |
| `git remote -v`               | Show remote URLs      |
| `git remote add origin <url>` | Add remote repo       |
| `git push origin <branch>`    | Upload changes        |
| `git push -u origin <branch>` | Push & set upstream   |
| `git pull`                    | Fetch + merge changes |
| `git fetch`                   | Download changes only |

______________________________________________
# Undoing & Fixing Mistakes:

| Command                       | Use                          |
| ----------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `git restore <file>`          | Undo file changes            |
| `git restore --staged <file>` | Unstage a file               |
| `git reset <file>`            | Unstage file (old way)       |
| `git reset --hard`            | Reset everything (dangerous) |
| `git revert <commit>`         | Undo commit safely           |
| `git checkout -- <file>`      | Discard file changes         |

______________________________________________
# Comparing Changes:

| Command                        | Use                  |
| ------------------------------ | -------------------- |
| `git diff`                     | See unstaged changes |
| `git diff --staged`            | See staged changes   |
| `git diff <branch1> <branch2>` | Compare branches     |

______________________________________________
# Stashing (Temporary Save):

| Command           | Use                      |
| ----------------- | ------------------------ |
| `git stash`       | Save changes temporarily |
| `git stash list`  | Show stashes             |
| `git stash apply` | Restore stash            |
| `git stash drop`  | Delete stash             |

______________________________________________
# Tags (Releases):

| Command                 | Use          |
| ----------------------- | ------------ |
| `git tag`               | List tags    |
| `git tag <name>`        | Create a tag |
| `git push origin <tag>` | Push tag     |

______________________________________________
10. Advanced / Less Common

| Command                    | Use                    |
| -------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| `git rebase <branch>`      | Reapply commits        |
| `git cherry-pick <commit>` | Copy a commit          |
| `git blame <file>`         | See who changed what   |
| `git show <commit>`        | View commit details    |
| `git clean -f`             | Remove untracked files |

______________________________________________
